<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<CommercialHero
  title="Commercial Outdoor Grill Burner Not Lighting, Same-Day Diagnostic"
  subtitle={`Restaurant patio, hotel buffet, catering grill won't light? Gas supply, spark, pilot, burner port. Wolf Outdoor, Lynx Pro Sear, Twin Eagles, MagiKitch'n. $120 commercial. ${phone}`}
  heroImageTitle="Commercial Grill Not Lighting"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Commercial grill ignition diagnostic</p>
    <h2>Commercial outdoor grill is distinct from residential. Different brands, duty cycle, and parts wear timing.</h2>

    <p>This page covers <strong>commercial outdoor grills</strong> at restaurant patios, hotel buffet stations, catering operations, country club outdoor kitchens, sports venue concessions. For <strong>residential outdoor grills</strong> (Lynx home, Wolf Outdoor home, Fire Magic, Twin Eagles home, Kalamazoo, Hestan, DCS, Alfresco) see <a href="/outdoor/grill-repair/">residential outdoor grill repair</a>.</p>

    <p>Commercial duty cycle (8 to 14 hours daily during operating season) accelerates parts wear roughly 5 to 10x residential. Burner port carbon clogs at year 2 to 3 vs year 6 to 8 residential. Spark modules fail at year 4 to 7 vs year 8 to 10 residential. Brand pool differs: Wolf Outdoor commercial (Middleby), Lynx Pro Sear and L-Series (Lynx Grills Compton CA), Twin Eagles commercial (Dometic Group Camarillo CA), MagiKitch'n outdoor (Middleby Wolf Industrial line).</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong>. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/grill-repair/">commercial grill repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Field observations</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top causes by frequency.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Gas supply pressure drop (peak demand on shared kitchen lines).</strong> Most common cause on restaurant patio installs sharing supply with indoor kitchen. $200-600 regulator-side fix.</li>
      <li><strong>Burner port carbon and grease buildup (year 2-3 commercial duty).</strong> $120-260 cleaning per burner section.</li>
      <li><strong>Spark module / spark electrode failure (electronic ignition, year 4-7).</strong> $260-440 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Pilot light / thermocouple failure (standing pilot, year 4-7).</strong> $220-340 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Hot surface igniter failure (HSI models, year 5-8).</strong> $280-440 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas valve safety lockout.</strong> $120 reset only.</li>
      <li><strong>Gas valve mechanical failure (year 7+).</strong> $480-680 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>LP commercial 100lb tank temperature drop in cold weather.</strong> Below 50°F ambient causes vapor production drop, regulator can't keep up. Operator-side fix (tank wraps, tank rotation).</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Diagnostic walkthrough</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Practitioner sequence.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Identify brand and model.</strong> Wolf Outdoor commercial Middleby vs Lynx Pro Sear vs Twin Eagles vs MagiKitch'n. Brand-specific parts and patterns.</li>
      <li><strong>Verify gas supply at unit.</strong> Isolation valve open, supply line uncompromised, manometer at inlet under load.</li>
      <li><strong>Identify ignition system type.</strong> Spark electronic, hot surface igniter, or standing pilot.</li>
      <li><strong>Visual burner port inspection.</strong> Carbon and grease buildup at orifices, asymmetric clogging.</li>
      <li><strong>Spark or pilot test.</strong> Visual spark / HSI glow / pilot flame strength.</li>
      <li><strong>Multimeter thermocouple under flame (standing pilot).</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Combustion quality verification.</strong> Blue steady flame at all burners.</li>
      <li><strong>LP tank inspection (LP installs).</strong> Tank temp, fill level, regulator condition.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Honest opinion</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Restaurant patio grill on shared supply: gas pressure first, every time.</h2>
    <p>About 25 percent of restaurant patio grill "won't light" calls resolve at gas-supply diagnostic, not appliance repair. The pattern: indoor kitchen and outdoor patio share a gas supply line, peak service hours pull total kitchen demand close to or above regulator capacity, patio grill gets pressure-starved first because it's furthest from the supply tap. Diagnostic is manometer at the patio grill inlet during full kitchen-load operation. If pressure drops below spec under that scenario, the fix is regulator-side (replumb or upsize regulator), $200 to $600 plumber-side. We test this on every restaurant patio grill call before quoting appliance parts.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Commercial grill burner-not-lighting costs.</h2>
